ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Any student working on the Ottoman empire should take this class. Obviously it wouldn't make sense for anyone else.
It's for students who want to read documents in Ottoman related to their research.
Ottoman class... well you need self-motivation and the routledge textbook will be useful.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Because I hope to work extensively and possibly primarily with Ottoman primary sources for my dissertation, and beyond, this course was absolutely fundamental for me in terms of developing the skills I need to do my work.
It helped me and others read difficult Ottoman texts in their originals.
